---
// Poster OAuth authorization page
---

<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Poster API Authorization</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 50px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        .auth-container {
            background: #f8f9fa;
            border: 1px solid #dee2e6;
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 30px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .auth-btn {
            background: #28a745;
            color: white;
            padding: 15px 30px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-size: 18px;
            cursor: pointer;
            text-decoration: none;
            display: inline-block;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
        .auth-btn:hover {
            background: #218838;
        }
        .info {
            background: #d1ecf1;
            border: 1px solid #bee5eb;
            color: #0c5460;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="auth-container">
        <h1>üîê Poster API Authorization</h1>
        
        <div class="info">
            <p><strong>About this authorization:</strong></p>
            <p>This will grant your application permission to:</p>
            <ul style="text-align: left;">
                <li>‚úÖ Read inventory data</li>
                <li>‚úÖ Create supply entries (POST permissions)</li>
                <li>‚úÖ Update storage inventory</li>
                <li>‚úÖ Access all developer API features</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <p>Click the button below to authorize with Poster:</p>
        
        <a href="/api/auth/poster-oauth" class="auth-btn">
            üöÄ Authorize with Poster
        </a>
        
        <div class="info">
            <p><strong>What happens next:</strong></p>
            <ol style="text-align: left;">
                <li>You'll be redirected to Poster's authorization page</li>
                <li>Log in to your Poster account and grant permissions</li>
                <li>You'll be redirected back with an access token</li>
                <li>Copy the token and update your application</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
        
        <p><em>Application ID: 4243</em></p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>